<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine Service, Model Year 1994 - 1998 - CYLINDER HEAD AND VALVES - Valve
        Springs - Inspection
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="recondition" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Inspection</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the inside and outside of the valve retainer keys for wear. Replace any worn
                retainer keys.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the valve springs for rust, pitting and cracks. Look for spring distortion.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1200447" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figcg1/cg15213.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Checking Free Length and Flatness of the Valve Spring</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check the free length and flatness of the valve springs. The spring ends must be flat and
                square. Springs that are out-of-square place a lateral load on the stem, causing accelerated valve guide
                wear.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1200448" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figcg1/cg11150.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Checking the Valve Spring Tension</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Linear Scale</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Valve Spring</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Load Indicator</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a valve spring tester to measure the valve spring tension. Apply the appropriate test
                load to each spring and refer to the specifications. Measure maximum spring length in use (valve closed)
                and the minimum spring length in use (valve open).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Replace any valve spring that is rusted, pitted, cracked, bent or incapable of meeting the
                specifications.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
